import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
Imports required libraries:
pandas → for data handling
matplotlib.pyplot → for plotting graphs
seaborn → for advanced visualization
df = sns.load_dataset("titanic")
Loads the built-in Titanic dataset into a DataFrame named df.
df.head()
Displays the first 5 rows of the dataset.
sns.boxplot(x='sex', y='age', hue='survived', data=df)
Creates a boxplot:
x='sex' → separates data by gender
y='age' → shows age distribution
hue='survived' → compares survived and non-survived passengers using different colors
Helps analyze how age and survival vary between males and females.
plt.xlabel('Gender')
plt.ylabel('Age')
plt.title('Age distribution by Gender and survived')
Adds labels and title to the graph.
plt.show()
Displays the final plot.
Conclusion

This program visualizes the age distribution of Titanic passengers based on gender and survival status using a boxplot.
Boxplot → Visualizes distribution and spread of numerical data.
Hue → Adds grouping by another category.
Outliers → Extreme values outside normal range.
Median → Middle value of dataset.
Quartiles → Divide data into four equal parts.
